>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>~</mo><mtext>N</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>5000</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>4750</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>868223</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>≈</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>868</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>86</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26495","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ1.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A statistician in the company suggests it would be fairer if the company passes the inspection when the mean weight of five randomly chosen bags is greater than 950 g. Find the pro","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.15—Central limit theorem"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}